        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="3">
            <title>HENDRICKSON TECHNICAL BULLETIN HN 402/462/522</title>
            <svcprocinfo>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">SUBJECT:</emph>
                    Auxiliary Spring Shim Design
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">LIT NO:</emph>
                    SEU-0100
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">DATE:</emph>
                    October 2000
                </para>
                <para>
                    <emph type="bold">REVISION:</emph>
                    A
                </para>
                <para>Effective November 3, 2000 an improved auxiliary spring assembly shim design will be in production
                    for the HN 402/462/522. The new design:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Addresses the importance of matching ride quality and stability for vocational
                            applications. Ride quality is subject to many influences in heavy-duty applications. They
                            include, but are not limited to: body equipment, rear suspension, cab suspension, terrain,
                            chassis/frame specifications, tires/wheels, front suspension, and wheelbase.
                        </para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Will be completely interchangeable with the current auxiliary spring system.</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Offers adjustability for a greater level of ride performance and handling.</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <para>All production vehicles will be equipped with a standard production assembly (see
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0003012">Figure 2</hotlnk>), using a (3) spacer shim system (compare to
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0003011">Prior Production Auxiliary Assembly</hotlnk>). A small percentage of
                    select vehicles will require a shim system other than the standard production assembly.
                </para>
                <para>An adjustment matrix below will assist in determining the correct amount of shims your vehicle
                    needs. The unladen tandem axle weight with the body installed is the primary determining factor for
                    a match to your vehicle and application.
                </para>
                <figure id="f0003011" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0003011.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="100"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1. Prior Production Auxiliary Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="f0003012" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../tsifigures/g0003012.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             resolution="100"/>
                    <caption>Figure 2. New Production Auxiliary Assembly</caption>
                </figure>
            </svcprocinfo>
            <svcsubproc>
                <title>Guidelines</title>
                <para>The following guidelines are essential in maximizing your suspension performance. If you have
                    questions contact Hendrickson Technical Services at 630.910.2800.
                </para>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">When ride quality is critical, and stability demands are less important, then fewer
                        spacer shim plates should be specified.
                    </para>
                </step1>
                <step1>
                    <para count="1">If on/off-highway stability is most important, then additional spacer shim plates
                        should be specified.
                    </para>
